text.344686: Bottom line is @elonmusk is a genius. If he can get this line running to 5k a week but really 10k a week. They will sell every car. This is an amazing car. Great job Elon. The tech is off he charts. Performance excellent. Beautiful design. A+ #tesla #model3 $tsla
text.344701: Basically everyone in the world is going to want this car. The price point is amazing for what you get. It’s the most advanced mass produced car ever made. At $55k it’s was worth it. At $35k for get about it. It will sell out forever. #tesla #model3 $tsla
text.344723: There are no visible manufacturing defects that I can find at this time. I was praying that there would not be dumb issues and there was none. The car is sweet. #tesla #model3 $tsla
text.344732: The interface is simple and Apple style. Takes 5 minutes to get set up & used to it.  My kid was working the screen in seconds. No keys or buttons is weird but amazing. Your phone is your key etc. plus it connects to the car and you can add more music like SiriusXM. #tesla $tsla
text.344743: The clear roofs and huge windshield gives you a large view of everything. Only thing is there is not a ton of visibility behind because of the way it’s designed but no one is passing you anyways. Cause you’re faster. I’m used to that from other cars. $tsla #model3 #tesla
text.344756: It’s really comfy. Great seats. The car feels substantial. Nothing cheap feeling in it. For $55k it kills the BMW and Mercedes of the same class. Good steering wheel. Plenty of room in the car. It’s minimalist and beautiful inside. #tesla #model3 $tsla
text.344769: It’s quiet. I came from a loud car with a huge engine. It’s amazing how quiet it is. But you lose track on how fast you’re going as it’s so responsive. I got to 100 quick and had to pull back for fear of getting pulled over. #tesla #model3 $tsla
text.344783: The car is fast. Faster than I thought. It jumps off the line like a tiger. It handled well I’m on 18” wheels. It brakes great. In fact you don’t use the breaks a lot because of regenerating breaking. When I slammed on them they worked fine. Stopped fast. #tesla #model3 $tsla
